I love the visual and music. My daughter loves it too. Japanese language option is great. One request for Japanese mode, please add "yomigana(pronounceation)" to Kanji characters. A lot of the Kanji characters used in this app are too difficult for 6-8 yrs old to know and read. (I couldn't read some of the names either..) for example, Èº† (mouse) is not commonly used Kanji and children won't learn in school. Love the app! The illustrations are loveable and cute. Just one suggestion: it would be more comfortable and convenient if the user didn't have to drag the magnifier to an item in order to read its information; instead he or she just needs to touch any items and info windows will appear. Hope you will make some adjustments to the app so that users would have nicer experience as using this amazing encyclopedia. Thanks!

This game is super, okay it costs a' little but it is worth it. You may be thinking are there any adds. There are no adds! And to all parents out there I tell ya you can learn from this game. So if you want you children to be smart then install it . Now it is mostly about science but what can you do if you don't know science. Exactly, nothing. And for the last time I will remind you. Install Little Mouse's Encyclopedia.

I'm a Daddy with two Boys, ages 5, and 3. They Love exploring with me in the Woods, dirt, animals, anything outside! Thanks for releasing this towards the end of a very long and, most of the time, too cold to play OUTSIDE. It helps with the feeling of being stuck inside, having the features, such as, Joyful WARM music, not extreme cartoon-like animation! Thank you, we will enjoy the next project you are working on... God Bless you, in The Name of The Father, The Son, and The Holy Spirit, AMEN.

I waited until the early morning of Feb 28 which was said to be its releasing date, but only found out many people already got it days before me! I really enjoy it, even though I am not a kid nor a mother yet üòÇ Great painting, very relaxing, and I can learn a lot about nature! Can't wait to see the update soon with more little mouse adventures!

Excellent learning game for our toddler! He calls the game "mouse." He especially loves all the animations and the magnifying glass feature is an excellent way to talk about all the game animals and entities with him. It is so simple because the learning is not forced and is interactive. FYI we have been playing Aniscience for a while, the previous version, and have found no other games like this. looking forward to more apps from this developer they have something unique here.
Beautiful app, worth the cost. We started with the free version (Aniscience) and the kids loved it so much, I had to buy this as soon as it came out. :)
